&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;CONSULTANT IN OBSTETRICS with interest in Maternal / Fetal Medicine&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a Consultant in Obstetrics with an interest in fetal medicine to join a highly regarded team within a large teaching hospital and a Level 2 Fetal Medicine Centre. The post-holder will be required to provide the full range of obstetric skills working in collaboration with existing consultants and within the multi-disciplinary team.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post is based at University Hospital of North Midlands. Clinical Duties will be across both the Royal Stoke and County Hospital Sites.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The University Hospital is the main teaching hospital for the Keele University Undergraduate Medical School and there are close ties with the University of Keele and Staffordshire University.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have MRCOG or appropriate specialist qualification and have completed RCOG. The candidate will also have CCST or equivalent (‘equivalence’ must be confirmed by PMETB/GMC by date of interview) and have entry onto the GMC Specialist Register or eligibility for entry within 6 months of date of interview and also have evidence of Fetal Medicine ATSM or equivalent.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Closing date: 23rd November 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview date: 14th December 2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Please note that we are currently awaiting approval of the Job Pack from the RCoG.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
